{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":0,"text":"Gabriel García Márquez is one of my favorite writers,"},{"time":2000,"text":"for his storytelling,"},{"time":4000,"text":"but even more, I think,"},{"time":6000,"text":"for the beauty and precision of his prose."},{"time":8000,"text":"And whether it's the opening line from \"One Hundred Years of Solitude\""},{"time":12000,"text":"or the fantastical stream of consciousness"},{"time":14000,"text":"in \"Autumn of the Patriarch,\""},{"time":16000,"text":"where the words rush by,"},{"time":18000,"text":"page after page of unpunctuated imagery"},{"time":20000,"text":"sweeping the reader along"},{"time":22000,"text":"like some wild river"},{"time":24000,"text":"twisting through a primal South American jungle,"},{"time":26000,"text":"reading Márquez is a visceral experience."},{"time":29000,"text":"Which struck me as particularly remarkable"},{"time":31000,"text":"during one session with the novel"},{"time":33000,"text":"when I realized that I was being swept along"},{"time":35000,"text":"on this remarkable, vivid journey"},{"time":38000,"text":"in translation."}]},{"cues":[{"time":40000,"text":"Now I was a comparative literature major in college,"},{"time":42000,"text":"which is like an English major,"},{"time":44000,"text":"only instead of being stuck studying Chaucer for three months,"},{"time":46000,"text":"we got to read great literature in translation"},{"time":48000,"text":"from around the world."},{"time":50000,"text":"And as great as these books were,"},{"time":52000,"text":"you could always tell"},{"time":54000,"text":"that you were getting close to the full effect."},{"time":56000,"text":"But not so with Márquez"},{"time":58000,"text":"who once praised his translator's versions"},{"time":60000,"text":"as being better than his own,"},{"time":63000,"text":"which is an astonishing compliment."}]},{"cues":[{"time":66000,"text":"So when I heard that the translator, Gregory Rabassa,"},{"time":68000,"text":"had written his own book on the subject,"},{"time":70000,"text":"I couldn't wait to read it."},{"time":72000,"text":"It's called apropos of the Italian adage"},{"time":74000,"text":"that I lifted from his forward,"},{"time":76000,"text":"\"If This Be Treason.\""},{"time":78000,"text":"And it's a charming read."},{"time":80000,"text":"It's highly recommended for anyone who's interested"},{"time":82000,"text":"in the translator's art."},{"time":84000,"text":"But the reason that I mention it"},{"time":86000,"text":"is that early on, Rabassa offers"},{"time":88000,"text":"this elegantly simple insight:"},{"time":92000,"text":"\"Every act of communication"},{"time":94000,"text":"is an act of translation.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":97000,"text":"Now maybe that's been obvious to all of you for a long time,"},{"time":100000,"text":"but for me,"},{"time":102000,"text":"as often as I'd encountered"},{"time":104000,"text":"that exact difficulty on a daily basis,"},{"time":106000,"text":"I had never seen the inherent challenge of communication"},{"time":109000,"text":"in so crystalline a light."},{"time":111000,"text":"Ever since I can remember"},{"time":113000,"text":"thinking consciously about such things,"},{"time":115000,"text":"communication has been my central passion."},{"time":117000,"text":"Even as a child,"},{"time":119000,"text":"I remember thinking that what I really wanted most in life"},{"time":122000,"text":"was to be able to understand everything"},{"time":125000,"text":"and then to communicate it to everyone else."},{"time":128000,"text":"So no ego problems."},{"time":131000,"text":"It's funny, my wife, Daisy,"},{"time":133000,"text":"whose family is littered with schizophrenics --"},{"time":135000,"text":"and I mean littered with them --"},{"time":138000,"text":"once said to me, \"Chris, I already have a brother who thinks he's God."},{"time":142000,"text":"I don't need a husband who wants to be.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":144000,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":146000,"text":"Anyway, as I plunged through my 20s"},{"time":148000,"text":"ever more aware of how unobtainable"},{"time":150000,"text":"the first part of my childhood ambition was,"},{"time":153000,"text":"it was that second part,"},{"time":155000,"text":"being able to successfully communicate to others"},{"time":157000,"text":"whatever knowledge I was gaining,"},{"time":159000,"text":"where the futility of my quest really set in."},{"time":162000,"text":"Time after time,"},{"time":164000,"text":"whenever I set out to share some great truth"},{"time":166000,"text":"with a soon-to-be grateful recipient,"},{"time":168000,"text":"it had the opposite effect."},{"time":171000,"text":"Interestingly, when your opening line of communication is,"},{"time":173000,"text":"\"Hey, listen up,"},{"time":175000,"text":"because I'm about to drop some serious knowledge on you,\""},{"time":179000,"text":"it's amazing how quickly you'll discover"},{"time":181000,"text":"both ice and the firing squad."}]},{"cues":[{"time":185000,"text":"Finally, after about 10 years"},{"time":187000,"text":"of alienating friends and strangers alike,"},{"time":190000,"text":"I finally got it,"},{"time":192000,"text":"a new personal truth all my own,"},{"time":195000,"text":"that if I was going to ever communicate well with other people"},{"time":199000,"text":"the ideas that I was gaining,"},{"time":201000,"text":"I'd better find a different way of going about it."},{"time":203000,"text":"And that's when I discovered comedy."}]},{"cues":[{"time":206000,"text":"Now comedy travels along a distinct wavelength"},{"time":209000,"text":"from other forms of language."},{"time":211000,"text":"If I had to place it on an arbitrary spectrum,"},{"time":213000,"text":"I'd say it falls somewhere"},{"time":215000,"text":"between poetry and lies."},{"time":219000,"text":"And I'm not talking about all comedy here,"},{"time":221000,"text":"because, clearly, there's plenty of humor"},{"time":223000,"text":"that colors safely within the lines of what we already think and feel."},{"time":226000,"text":"What I want to talk about"},{"time":228000,"text":"is the unique ability that the best comedy and satire has"},{"time":231000,"text":"at circumventing our ingrained perspectives --"},{"time":234000,"text":"comedy as the philosopher's stone."},{"time":237000,"text":"It takes the base metal of our conventional wisdom"},{"time":240000,"text":"and transforms it through ridicule"},{"time":242000,"text":"into a different way of seeing"},{"time":244000,"text":"and ultimately being in the world."},{"time":246000,"text":"Because that's what I take"},{"time":248000,"text":"from the theme of this conference: Gained in Translation."},{"time":251000,"text":"That it's about communication"},{"time":253000,"text":"that doesn't just produce greater understanding"},{"time":255000,"text":"within the individual,"},{"time":257000,"text":"but leads to real change."},{"time":259000,"text":"Which in my experience means communication"},{"time":261000,"text":"that manages to speak to and expand"},{"time":264000,"text":"our concept of self-interest."},{"time":267000,"text":"Now I'm big on speaking to people's self-interest"},{"time":269000,"text":"because we're all wired for that."},{"time":271000,"text":"It's part of our survival package,"},{"time":273000,"text":"and that's why it's become so important for us,"},{"time":276000,"text":"and that's why we're always listening at that level."},{"time":279000,"text":"And also because that's where,"},{"time":282000,"text":"in terms of our own self-interest,"},{"time":284000,"text":"we finally begin to grasp"},{"time":286000,"text":"our ability to respond, our responsibility"},{"time":289000,"text":"to the rest of the world."}]},{"cues":[{"time":291000,"text":"Now as to what I mean by the best comedy and satire,"},{"time":294000,"text":"I mean work that comes first and foremost"},{"time":296000,"text":"from a place of honesty and integrity."},{"time":299000,"text":"Now if you think back"},{"time":301000,"text":"on Tina Fey's impersonations on Saturday Night Live"},{"time":304000,"text":"of the newly nominated vice presidential candidate"},{"time":306000,"text":"Sarah Palin,"},{"time":308000,"text":"they were devastating."},{"time":310000,"text":"Fey demonstrated far more effectively than any political pundit"},{"time":313000,"text":"the candidate's fundamental lack of seriousness,"},{"time":316000,"text":"cementing an impression"},{"time":318000,"text":"that the majority of the American public still holds today."},{"time":321000,"text":"And the key detail of this"},{"time":323000,"text":"is that Fey's scripts weren't written by her"},{"time":325000,"text":"and they weren't written by the SNL writers."},{"time":327000,"text":"They were lifted verbatim"},{"time":329000,"text":"from Palin's own remarks."},{"time":331000,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":335000,"text":"Here was a Palin impersonator"},{"time":337000,"text":"quoting Palin word for word."},{"time":339000,"text":"Now that's honesty and integrity,"},{"time":341000,"text":"and it's also why Fey's performances"},{"time":343000,"text":"left such a lasting impression."}]},{"cues":[{"time":345000,"text":"On the other side of the political spectrum,"},{"time":348000,"text":"the first time that I heard Rush Limbaugh"},{"time":350000,"text":"refer to presidential hopeful John Edwards as the Breck girl"},{"time":354000,"text":"I knew that he'd made a direct hit."},{"time":357000,"text":"Now it's not often that I'm going to associate"},{"time":359000,"text":"the words honesty and integrity with Limbaugh,"},{"time":362000,"text":"but it's really hard to argue with that punchline."},{"time":365000,"text":"The description perfectly captured"},{"time":367000,"text":"Edwards' personal vanity."},{"time":369000,"text":"And guess what?"},{"time":371000,"text":"That ended up being the exact personality trait"},{"time":373000,"text":"that was at the core of the scandal that ended his political career."}]},{"cues":[{"time":378000,"text":"Now The Daily Show with John Stewart"},{"time":380000,"text":"is by far the most --"},{"time":382000,"text":"(Applause)"},{"time":389000,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":391000,"text":"it's by far the most well-documented example"},{"time":394000,"text":"of the effectiveness of this kind of comedy."},{"time":397000,"text":"Survey after survey,"},{"time":399000,"text":"from Pew Research to the Annenberg Center for Public Policy,"},{"time":402000,"text":"has found that Daily Show viewers are better informed about current events"},{"time":405000,"text":"than the viewers of all major network and cable news shows."}]},{"cues":[{"time":409000,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":412000,"text":"Now whether this says more"},{"time":414000,"text":"about the conflict between integrity and profitability"},{"time":417000,"text":"of corporate journalism"},{"time":419000,"text":"than it does about the attentiveness of Stewart's viewers,"},{"time":421000,"text":"the larger point remains"},{"time":423000,"text":"that Stewart's material"},{"time":425000,"text":"is always grounded in a commitment to the facts --"},{"time":428000,"text":"not because his intent is to inform. It's not."},{"time":430000,"text":"His intent is to be funny."},{"time":432000,"text":"It just so happens that Stewart's brand of funny"},{"time":435000,"text":"doesn't work unless the facts are true."},{"time":438000,"text":"And the result is great comedy"},{"time":440000,"text":"that's also an information delivery system"},{"time":443000,"text":"that scores markedly higher in both credibility and retention"},{"time":446000,"text":"than the professional news media."},{"time":449000,"text":"Now this is doubly ironic"},{"time":451000,"text":"when you consider that what gives comedy its edge"},{"time":454000,"text":"at reaching around people's walls"},{"time":456000,"text":"is the way that it uses deliberate misdirection."}]},{"cues":[{"time":459000,"text":"A great piece of comedy is a verbal magic trick,"},{"time":462000,"text":"where you think it's going over here"},{"time":464000,"text":"and then all of a sudden you're transported over here."},{"time":467000,"text":"And there's this mental delight"},{"time":469000,"text":"that's followed by the physical response of laughter,"},{"time":471000,"text":"which, not coincidentally,"},{"time":473000,"text":"releases endorphins in the brain."},{"time":475000,"text":"And just like that, you've been seduced"},{"time":477000,"text":"into a different way of looking at something"},{"time":479000,"text":"because the endorphins have brought down your defenses."},{"time":482000,"text":"This is the exact opposite"},{"time":484000,"text":"of the way that anger and fear and panic,"},{"time":486000,"text":"all of the flight-or-fight responses, operate."},{"time":489000,"text":"Flight-or-fight releases adrenalin,"},{"time":492000,"text":"which throws our walls up sky-high."},{"time":494000,"text":"And the comedy comes along,"},{"time":496000,"text":"dealing with a lot of the same areas"},{"time":498000,"text":"where our defenses are the strongest --"},{"time":500000,"text":"race, religion, politics, sexuality --"},{"time":503000,"text":"only by approaching them through humor instead of adrenalin,"},{"time":506000,"text":"we get endorphins"},{"time":508000,"text":"and the alchemy of laughter turns our walls into windows,"},{"time":511000,"text":"revealing a fresh and unexpected point of view."}]},{"cues":[{"time":514000,"text":"Now let me give you an example from my act."},{"time":517000,"text":"I have some material"},{"time":519000,"text":"about the so-called radical gay agenda,"},{"time":521000,"text":"which starts off by asking,"},{"time":523000,"text":"how radical is the gay agenda?"},{"time":525000,"text":"Because from what I can tell, the three things gay Americans seem to want most"},{"time":528000,"text":"are to join the military, get married and start a family."},{"time":531000,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":535000,"text":"Three things I've tried to avoid my entire life."},{"time":539000,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":541000,"text":"Have at it you radical bastards. The field is yours."}]},{"cues":[{"time":544000,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":547000,"text":"And that's followed by these lines"},{"time":549000,"text":"about gay adoption:"},{"time":551000,"text":"What is the problem with gay adoption?"},{"time":553000,"text":"Why is this remotely controversial?"},{"time":555000,"text":"If you have a baby and you think that baby's gay,"},{"time":558000,"text":"you should be allowed to put it up for adoption."},{"time":560000,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":562000,"text":"You have given birth to an abomination."},{"time":564000,"text":"Remove it from your household."},{"time":568000,"text":"Now by taking the biblical epithet \"abomination\""},{"time":571000,"text":"and attaching it to the ultimate image of innocence, a baby,"},{"time":575000,"text":"this joke short circuits the emotional wiring"},{"time":577000,"text":"behind the debate"},{"time":579000,"text":"and it leaves the audience with the opportunity, through their laughter,"},{"time":582000,"text":"to question its validity."}]},{"cues":[{"time":584000,"text":"Misdirection isn't the only trick"},{"time":586000,"text":"that comedy has up its sleeve."},{"time":588000,"text":"Economy of language"},{"time":590000,"text":"is another real strong suit of great comedy."},{"time":592000,"text":"There are few phrases"},{"time":594000,"text":"that pack a more concentrated dose of subject and symbol"},{"time":597000,"text":"than the perfect punchline."},{"time":599000,"text":"Bill Hicks -- and if you don't know his work,"},{"time":601000,"text":"you should really Google him --"},{"time":603000,"text":"Hicks had a routine"},{"time":605000,"text":"about getting into one of those childhood bragging contests on the playground,"},{"time":608000,"text":"where finally the other kid says to him,"},{"time":610000,"text":"\"Huh? Well my dad can beat up your dad,\""},{"time":613000,"text":"to which Hicks replies,"},{"time":615000,"text":"\"Really? How soon?\""},{"time":617000,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":622000,"text":"That's an entire childhood"},{"time":624000,"text":"in three words."},{"time":626000,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":629000,"text":"Not to mention what it reveals"},{"time":631000,"text":"about the adult who's speaking them."}]},{"cues":[{"time":633000,"text":"And one last powerful attribute"},{"time":635000,"text":"that comedy has as communication"},{"time":637000,"text":"is that it's inherently viral."},{"time":639000,"text":"People can't wait"},{"time":641000,"text":"to pass along that new great joke."},{"time":643000,"text":"And this isn't some new phenomenon of our wired world."},{"time":646000,"text":"Comedy has been crossing country"},{"time":648000,"text":"with remarkable speed"},{"time":650000,"text":"way before the Internet, social media,"},{"time":652000,"text":"even cable TV."},{"time":654000,"text":"Back in 1980"},{"time":656000,"text":"when comedian Richard Pryor accidentally set himself on fire"},{"time":659000,"text":"during a freebasing accident,"},{"time":661000,"text":"I was in Los Angeles the day after it happened"},{"time":663000,"text":"and then I was in Washington D.C. two days after that."},{"time":667000,"text":"And I heard the exact same punchline on both coasts --"},{"time":670000,"text":"something about the Ignited Negro College Fund."},{"time":674000,"text":"Clearly, it didn't come out of a Tonight Show monologue."},{"time":678000,"text":"And my guess here -- and I have no research on this --"},{"time":680000,"text":"is that if you really were to look back at it and if you could research it,"},{"time":683000,"text":"you'd find out that comedy"},{"time":685000,"text":"is the second oldest viral profession."},{"time":687000,"text":"First there were drums"},{"time":689000,"text":"and then knock-knock jokes."}]},{"cues":[{"time":691000,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":693000,"text":"But it's when you put all of these elements together --"},{"time":696000,"text":"when you get the viral appeal of a great joke"},{"time":699000,"text":"with a powerful punchline"},{"time":701000,"text":"that's crafted from honesty and integrity,"},{"time":703000,"text":"it can have a real world impact"},{"time":706000,"text":"at changing a conversation."},{"time":708000,"text":"Now I have a close friend, Joel Pett,"},{"time":710000,"text":"who's the editorial cartoonist"},{"time":712000,"text":"for the Lexington Herald-Leader."},{"time":714000,"text":"And he used to be the USA Today Monday morning guy."},{"time":717000,"text":"I was visiting with Joel"},{"time":719000,"text":"the weekend before the Copenhagen conference on climate change opened"},{"time":722000,"text":"in December of 2009."},{"time":724000,"text":"And Joel was explaining to me"},{"time":726000,"text":"that, because USA Today"},{"time":728000,"text":"was one of America's four papers of record,"},{"time":730000,"text":"it would be scanned by virtually everyone in attendance at the conference,"},{"time":734000,"text":"which meant that, if he hit it out of the park with his cartoon"},{"time":737000,"text":"on Monday, the opening day of the conference,"},{"time":739000,"text":"it could get passed around"},{"time":741000,"text":"at the highest level among actual decision-makers."}]},{"cues":[{"time":744000,"text":"So we started talking about climate change."},{"time":747000,"text":"And it turned out that Joel and I"},{"time":749000,"text":"were both bothered by the same thing,"},{"time":751000,"text":"which was how so much of the debate"},{"time":753000,"text":"was still focused on the science"},{"time":755000,"text":"and how complete it was or wasn't,"},{"time":757000,"text":"which, to both of us,"},{"time":759000,"text":"seems somewhat intentionally off point."},{"time":762000,"text":"Because first of all, there's this false premise"},{"time":765000,"text":"that such a thing as complete science exists."},{"time":769000,"text":"Now Governor Perry of my newly-adopted state of Texas"},{"time":772000,"text":"was pushing this same line this past summer"},{"time":775000,"text":"at the beginning of his oops-fated campaign"},{"time":779000,"text":"for the Republican presidential nomination,"},{"time":782000,"text":"proclaiming over and over that the science wasn't complete"},{"time":785000,"text":"at the same time that 250"},{"time":788000,"text":"out of 254 counties in the state of Texas"},{"time":791000,"text":"were on fire."},{"time":794000,"text":"And Perry's policy solution"},{"time":796000,"text":"was to ask the people of Texas"},{"time":798000,"text":"to pray for rain."},{"time":801000,"text":"Personally, I was praying for four more fires"},{"time":803000,"text":"so we could finally complete the damn science."}]},{"cues":[{"time":806000,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":811000,"text":"But back in 2009,"},{"time":813000,"text":"the question Joel and I kept turning over and over"},{"time":816000,"text":"was why this late in the game"},{"time":818000,"text":"so much energy was being spent talking about the science"},{"time":821000,"text":"when the policies necessary to address climate change"},{"time":824000,"text":"were unequivocally beneficial for humanity in the long run"},{"time":828000,"text":"regardless of the science."},{"time":830000,"text":"So we tossed it back and forth until Joel came up with this."},{"time":833000,"text":"Cartoon: \"What if it's a big hoax and we create a better world for nothing?\""},{"time":841000,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":844000,"text":"You've got to love that idea."},{"time":846000,"text":"(Applause)"},{"time":853000,"text":"How about that? How about we create a better world for nothing?"},{"time":857000,"text":"Not for God, not for country, not for profit --"},{"time":860000,"text":"just as a basic metric for global decision-making."}]},{"cues":[{"time":864000,"text":"And this cartoon hit the bull's eye."},{"time":867000,"text":"Shortly after the conference was over,"},{"time":869000,"text":"Joel got a request for a signed copy"},{"time":871000,"text":"from the head of the EPA in Washington"},{"time":873000,"text":"whose wall it now hangs on."},{"time":875000,"text":"And not long after that, he got another request for a copy"},{"time":878000,"text":"from the head of the EPA in California"},{"time":880000,"text":"who used it as part of her presentation"},{"time":883000,"text":"at an international conference on climate change"},{"time":886000,"text":"in Sacramento last year."},{"time":888000,"text":"And it didn't stop there."},{"time":890000,"text":"To date, Joel's gotten requests from over 40 environmental groups,"},{"time":893000,"text":"in the United States, Canada and Europe."},{"time":896000,"text":"And earlier this year,"},{"time":898000,"text":"he got a request from the Green Party in Australia"},{"time":900000,"text":"who used it in their campaign"},{"time":902000,"text":"where it became part of the debate"},{"time":904000,"text":"that resulted in the Australian parliament"},{"time":907000,"text":"adopting the most rigorous carbon tax regime"},{"time":909000,"text":"of any country in the world."},{"time":912000,"text":"(Applause)"},{"time":917000,"text":"That is a lot of punch"},{"time":919000,"text":"for 14 words."}]},{"cues":[{"time":922000,"text":"So my suggestion to those of you out here"},{"time":924000,"text":"who are seriously focused on creating a better world"},{"time":927000,"text":"is to take a little bit of time each day"},{"time":929000,"text":"and practice thinking funny,"},{"time":932000,"text":"because you might just find the question that you've been looking for."}]},{"cues":[{"time":935000,"text":"Thank you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":937000,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}